# Stanton Management — Windsurf Rules

---

## 1. Architecture First

Before writing any code, understand what is being built and where it belongs in the system. A working solution that fits badly is not a solution.

- When something doesn't work inside a container, question the container before patching the component
- If you've tried the same fix twice and it hasn't worked, stop — the approach is wrong, not the fix
- Never treat a workaround as a deliverable
- Do not add conditionals to an existing component when the correct answer is a new component
- Do not hardcode values that belong in config
- Do not duplicate logic that belongs in a shared hook or utility

---

## 2. Components — Look Before You Build

Before writing any UI, check for existing components:

1. `@/components/kit/` — general UI primitives
2. `@/components/form/` — all form elements

If a component exists that covers the use case, use it. Do not inline equivalent markup. Only create a new component if nothing in the kit fits — and if you do, build it to the same standard so it belongs in the kit.

---

## 3. Design System

All visual decisions come from the design system. No exceptions.

- CSS custom properties for all colors — no hardcoded hex, no arbitrary Tailwind values
- `rounded-none` on all inputs and buttons — no border radius
- Serif fonts (`Libre Baskerville`) for headers only — `Inter` for everything else
- Institutional aesthetic — no vibrant colors, no bouncing animations, no startup patterns
- Transitions: 200–300ms ease-out only
- Spacing from the defined scale — no arbitrary pixel values

---

## 4. Database Rules

- All new payroll tables prefixed `payroll_`
- Read from canonical tables only — never query `AF_` staging tables directly
- Never write to AF-Authoritative columns (`tenants`, `work_orders`, `inspections`, `leases`)
- FK to `properties`, `portfolios`, `units` from canonical tables — never duplicate these entities
- RLS required on every new table — no exceptions
- No hard deletes — use `is_current = false`
- Money: `NUMERIC(10,2)`
- Status columns: lowercase TEXT with CHECK constraint
- Every table needs `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`
- `updated_at` uses `trigger_set_updated_at()` — the function already exists

---

## 5. Layout & Sizing Decisions Are Local

A layout rule made for one page does not apply to other pages. Never carry a sizing, width, or spacing constraint from one context to another without re-evaluating it in the new context.

- Table width should fit the data it contains and the space available on that specific page
- A component that works correctly when rendered standalone should not be distorted to fit a container — change the container
- If a previous suggestion is causing a problem in a new context, surface the conflict rather than silently applying the old rule

---

## 6. Supabase Patterns

- Queries go in hooks — no raw Supabase calls inside components
- One hook per logical data domain
- Always handle loading, error, and empty states explicitly
- Realtime subscriptions must be cleaned up on unmount

---

## 7. When Stuck

If a problem isn't resolving after two attempts:
- State what approach was tried and why it isn't working
- Propose an alternative approach before continuing
- Do not re-attempt the same fix with minor variations
